RESULTED IN AN INCREASE OF APPROXIMATELY $22 MILLION

IN PREVIOUSLY REPORTED OPENING ADDITIONAL PAID IN CAPITAL AND A CORRESPONDING

DECREASE IN PREVIOUSLY REPORTED OPENING RETAINED EARNINGS.

IN

EARLY OCTOBER 2008, THE FASB ISSUED AN ACCOUNTING STANDARD CODIFIED IN ASC

820,

FAIR VALUE MEASUREMENTS AND DISCLOSURES

,

WHICH ILLUSTRATED KEY CONSIDERATIONS IN DETERMINING THE FAIR VALUE OF A

FINANCIAL ASSET IN AN INACTIVE MARKET. THIS STANDARD WAS EFFECTIVE FOR 3M

BEGINNING WITH THE QUARTER ENDED SEPTEMBER 30, 2008. ITS ADDITIONAL

