AND CANOGA TRAFFIC DETECTION BUSINESSES TO TORQUEST PARTNERS INC., A

TORONTO-BASED INVESTMENT FIRM. 3M RECEIVED PROCEEDS OF $80 MILLION FOR THIS

TRANSACTION AND RECOGNIZED, NET OF ASSETS SOLD, TRANSACTION AND OTHER COSTS, A

PRE-TAX GAIN OF $68 MILLION (RECORDED IN THE DISPLAY AND GRAPHICS SEGMENT) IN

2007. IN JANUARY 2007, 3M COMPLETED THE SALE OF ITS GLOBAL BRANDED

PHARMACEUTICALS BUSINESS IN EUROPE TO MEDA AB. 3M RECEIVED PROCEEDS OF $817

MILLION FOR THIS TRANSACTION AND RECOGNIZED, NET OF ASSETS SOLD, A PRE-TAX GAIN

OF $781 MILLION (RECORDED IN THE HEALTH CARE SEGMENT) IN 2007.

IN

CONNECTION WITH THE PHARMACEUTICALS TRANSACTION, 3M ENTERED INTO AGREEMENTS

WHEREBY ITS DRUG DELIVERY SYSTEMS DIVISION BECAME A SOURCE OF SUPPLY TO THE

ACQUIRING COMPANY. BECAUSE OF THE EXTENT OF 3M CASH FLOWS FROM THESE

