OF CONTENTS

·

DURING THE THIRD QUARTER OF 2009, 3M

ANNOUNCED THE ELIMINATION OF APPROXIMATELY 200 POSITIONS, WITH THE MAJORITY OF THOSE OCCURRING IN WESTERN EUROPE

AND, TO A LESSER EXTENT, THE UNITED STATES. THESE RESTRUCTURING ACTIONS, INCLUDING A NON-CASH CHARGE RELATED TO A

PENSION SETTLEMENT IN JAPAN (DISCUSSED FURTHER IN NOTE 11), RESULTED IN A

THIRD-QUARTER 2009 NET PRE-TAX CHARGE OF $26 MILLION FOR EMPLOYEE-RELATED

ITEMS/BENEFITS AND OTHER, WHICH IS NET OF $7 MILLION OF ADJUSTMENTS TO PRIOR

2008 AND 2009 RESTRUCTURING ACTIONS. THE PRECEDING CHARGES WERE RECORDED

IN COST OF SALES ($25 MILLION) AND RESEARCH, DEVELOPMENT AND RELATED EXPENSES

($1 MILLION).

