NON-CASH

EMPLOYEE-RELATED CHANGES IN 2007 PRIMARILY RELATE TO SPECIAL TERMINATION

PENSION AND MEDICAL BENEFITS GRANTED TO CERTAIN U.S. ELIGIBLE EMPLOYEES. THESE

PENSION AND MEDICAL BENEFITS WERE REFLECTED AS A COMPONENT OF THE BENEFIT

OBLIGATION OF THE COMPANYS PENSION AND MEDICAL PLANS AS OF DECEMBER 31,

2007. IN ADDITION, THESE CHANGES ALSO REFLECT NON-CASH STOCK OPTION EXPENSE DUE

TO THE RECLASSIFICATION OF CERTAIN EMPLOYEES AGE 50 AND OLDER TO RETIREE

STATUS, RESULTING IN A MODIFICATION OF THEIR ORIGINAL STOCK OPTION AWARDS FOR

ACCOUNTING PURPOSES.

