THE COMPANY HAS NOT

PROVIDED DEFERRED TAXES ON UNREMITTED EARNINGS ATTRIBUTABLE TO INTERNATIONAL

COMPANIES THAT HAVE BEEN CONSIDERED TO BE REINVESTED INDEFINITELY. THESE

EARNINGS RELATE TO ONGOING OPERATIONS AND WERE APPROXIMATELY $5.6 BILLION AS OF

DECEMBER 31, 2009. BECAUSE OF THE AVAILABILITY OF U.S. FOREIGN TAX

CREDITS, IT IS NOT PRACTICABLE TO DETERMINE THE INCOME TAX LIABILITY THAT WOULD

BE PAYABLE IF SUCH EARNINGS WERE NOT INDEFINITELY REINVESTED.

